One embodiment of this invention, therefore, pertains to compounds that inhibit Aurora-kinases, the compounds having Formula I
and therapeutically acceptable salts thereof, wherein
X is S, O or NG1;
G1 is H or is alkyl
A1 is C(O)NHR1;
B1, C1, and D1 are independently selected OR1, H, F, Br, Cl, or I;
R1 is R2 or R5;
R2 is phenyl;
R5 is alkyl which is unsubstituted or substituted with one, two, three, four or five of independently selected R6, OH, F, Cl, Br or I;
R6 is R7 or R9;
R7 is phenyl;
R9 is heterocycloalkyl;
wherein each foregoing cyclic moiety is independently unsubstituted or substituted with one or two or three or four or five of independently selected R10, NHC(O)R10, NHC(O)NHR10, F, Cl, Br or I;
R10 is R11, R12 or R14;
R11 is phenyl;
R12 is heteroaryl;
R14 is alkyl which is unsubstituted or substituted with one, two, three, four or five of independently selected R15, NH2, NHC(O)R15, NHC(O)NHR15, F, Cl, Br or I;
R15 is R16, R17, R18 or R19;
R16 is phenyl;
R17 is heteroaryl;
R18 is cycloalkyl;
R19 is alkyl, each of which is substituted with R20;
R20 is phenyl;
wherein the moieties represented by R11, R12, R16, R17, R18 and R20 are independently unsubstituted or substituted with one or two or three of independently selected R21, OR21, SR21, CN, CF3, OCF3, F, Cl, Br or I; and
R21 is alkyl which is unsubstituted or substituted with one or two or three of independently selected F, Cl, Br, I, OH.

